tweet: But Martinez will have one chance for redemption after that awful bunt. Comes in the 9th inning. Bonds on first. One out. Pirates down 2-1.  Martinez works the count and then unleashes a rip to deep right center field. Exactly where he hit his double, only this one is better hit

tweet: Martinez inexplicably lays down a bunt - well, inexplicable by today‚Äôs standards.   Martinez had maybe put down 2 bunts his whole career. He pops up the pitch. First out. Next 2 guys hit fly balls for outs that, had the bunt worked, both would‚Äôve scored the runners on sac flies

tweet: The Pirates only recorded one hit in the game, an RBI double from Martinez that tied the game in the 5th inning.  Fast forward to the top of the 7th. Game still tied 1-1. Martinez steps up to bat with Bonilla at 2nd and Bonds at 1st. No outs.

name: Allan Smith
tweet: Martinez had a very brief career with the Pirates, only appearing in 25 combined regular and postseason games. But he did enjoy a 9-year big league career with more than 1,000 plate appearances and 100 home runs.  But now, to his Game 6 performance

tweet: Martinez had, in my estimation, one of the most absurd games in a high-stakes do-or-die scenario. And it‚Äôs never discussed  Basically nothing written on his performance in the decades that followed. Have never heard him discussed
